@page "/Numeric-TextBox/Default-Functionalities"

@using Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs

@inherits SampleBaseComponent;
@*Hidden:Lines*@
@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager
<PageTitle>Blazor Numeric Textbox Default Functionalities Example - Syncfusion Demos</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="This example demonstrates the Default Functionalities in Blazor Numeric Textbox Component. Explore here for more details." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="@canonicalURL" />
</HeadContent>
@*End:Hidden*@

<SampleDescription>
    <p>This example demonstrates the default functionalities of the <a href='https://www.syncfusion.com/blazor-components/blazor-numeric-textbox/'>Numeric Textbox</a>. Type a value in the input element to change the value dynamically, or press up/down arrow button to increase/decrease the value with a predefined step value.</p>
</SampleDescription>
<ActionDescription>
    <p>The Numeric Textbox provides an option to customize the display format of the numeric value using the <a href='https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/blazor/Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfNumericTextBox-1.html#Syncfusion_Blazor_Inputs_SfNumericTextBox_1_Format' target='_blank'>Format</a> property. It accepts the standard numeric format string and custom numeric format string as specified in <a target='_blank'href='https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/base-types/standard-numeric-format-strings'>MSDN</a>. The formatted value displays when the component is not focused.</p>
    <p>The Numeric Textbox component is used to get the number inputs from the user. The input values can be increased or decreased with a predefined step value.</p>
    <p>In this demo, the default Numeric Textbox is rendered with the percent and currency formats as specified in <a target='_blank'href='https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/base-types/standard-numeric-format-strings'>MSDN</a>.</p>
    <p><b>See also</b></p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href='https://blazor.syncfusion.com/documentation/numeric-textbox/getting-started/' target='_blank'>Getting started with Blazor Numeric Textbox</a></li>
        <li><a href='https://blazor.syncfusion.com/documentation/numeric-textbox/formats' target='_blank'>Blazor Numeric Textbox - Number Formats</a></li>
    </ul>
</ActionDescription>

<div class="col-lg-12 control-section">
    <div class="control-wrapper">
        <div class="example-content">
            <label class="example-label">Number format</label>
            <SfNumericTextBox TValue="double?" Value=10></SfNumericTextBox>
        </div>
        <div class="example-content">
            <label class="example-label">Percentage</label>
            <SfNumericTextBox TValue="double?" Format="p2" Value=0.5 Max=1 Min=0 Step=0.01></SfNumericTextBox>
        </div>
        <div class="example-content">
            <label class="example-label">Currency format</label>
            <SfNumericTextBox TValue="double?" Format="c2" Value=100></SfNumericTextBox>
        </div>    
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .control-wrapper {
        max-width: 230px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 0px 0px;
    }

    .example-label {
        font-size: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .example-content {
        padding: 0px 0px 20px 0px;
    }

    .example-content:last-child {
        padding: 0px 0px 40px 0px;
    }
</style>

@*Hidden:Lines*@
@code {
    private string canonicalURL { get; set; }

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        canonicalURL = NavigationManager.Uri.Split("?")[0];
    }
}
@*End:Hidden*@
